/* ============================================================
   pgbd.casa custom styles

   Typography is hybrid by design:
   - Body and most headings use Atkinson Hyperlegible, a sans-
     serif designed by the Braille Institute for low-vision and
     dyslexic readers. Letters are visually distinct (no I/l/1
     collisions, no b/d mirroring) which helps every reader, not
     just dyslexic ones. Switched here from MonoLisa Italic + SS02
     (cursive script) which was a real readability barrier.
     See BUG-016.
   - Page titles styled like a terminal prompt (e.g.
     `Σ ~/sala  # About Me`) and the typeit typing animations stay
     in MonoLisa upright. The terminal-prompt look is the
     identity-defining typography. Upright (not italic) is fine
     for short H1s; italic cursive was the dyslexia issue.
   - Code blocks use MonoLisa upright with ligatures, unchanged.
   ============================================================ */

@font-face {
  font-family: 'Atkinson Hyperlegible';
  src: url('/fonts/AtkinsonHyperlegible-Regular.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-weight: 400;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}

@font-face {
  font-family: 'Atkinson Hyperlegible';
  src: url('/fonts/AtkinsonHyperlegible-Italic.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-weight: 400;
  font-style: italic;
  font-display: swap;
}

@font-face {
  font-family: 'Atkinson Hyperlegible';
  src: url('/fonts/AtkinsonHyperlegible-Bold.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-weight: 700;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}

@font-face {
  font-family: 'Atkinson Hyperlegible';
  src: url('/fonts/AtkinsonHyperlegible-BoldItalic.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-weight: 700;
  font-style: italic;
  font-display: swap;
}

@font-face {
  font-family: 'MonoLisa';
  src: url('/fonts/MonoLisaVariable.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-weight: 100 900;
  font-style: normal;
  font-display: swap;
}

/* Body: Atkinson sans-serif. Italic kept for emphasis only. */
html, body {
  font-family: 'Atkinson Hyperlegible', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
  font-style: normal;
  font-feature-settings: normal;
}

/* Most headings: Atkinson sans-serif (clean, modern, readable). */
h2, h3, h4, h5, h6 {
  font-family: 'Atkinson Hyperlegible', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
  font-style: normal;
}

/* H1 page titles and typing animations: MonoLisa upright.
   These are the terminal-prompt strings (e.g. `Σ ~/sala  # About Me`)
   and the {{< typeit >}} cycling animations. Keeping the monospace
   look here preserves the identity-defining typography, while body
   prose gets the Atkinson readability win. */
h1,
[id^="typeit-"] {
  font-family: 'MonoLisa', ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', Menlo, Consolas, monospace;
  font-style: normal;
  font-feature-settings: "ss02" 0, "calt" 1, "liga" 1;
}

/* Code blocks: MonoLisa upright with ligatures, unchanged. */
code, pre, kbd, samp,
.highlight, .highlight pre, .highlight code {
  font-family: 'MonoLisa', ui-monospace, 'SF Mono', Menlo, Consolas, monospace !important;
  font-style: normal !important;
  font-feature-settings: "ss02" 0, "calt" 1, "liga" 1, "zero" 1 !important;
}

/* Timeline badges - prevent date range wrapping. Targets Blowfish badge spans which use Tailwind utility classes. */
span.rounded-md.border-primary-400 {
  white-space: nowrap !important;
}

/* Center Mermaid diagrams and figures */
.mermaid,
figure,
.prose p > img:only-child {
  display: flex;
  justify-content: center;
  margin: 1.5rem auto;
}

/* ============================================================
   Mobile fix: timeline header/badge overflow on narrow viewports.
   The Blowfish timelineItem shortcode renders the entry header
   and date badge in a `flex justify-between` row. With nowrap on
   the badge, the row demands more width than a phone viewport.
   The parent card is flex-1 with default min-width:auto, so it
   cannot shrink below that width and the entire card overflows
   horizontally, clipping body text against the right edge.
   Fix: under 640px, stack header above badge and allow the card
   to shrink below its natural content width.
   ============================================================ */
@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .shadow-2xl.flex-1.ms-6 > .flex.justify-between {
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.5rem;
  }
  .shadow-2xl.flex-1.ms-6 {
    min-width: 0;
  }
}

/* ============================================================
   Mobile fix: typing-animation lead overflow on narrow viewports.
   The {{< typeit >}} animation grows letter-by-letter; at full
   string width on a phone, longer language variants (Greek
   `Τα Pipelines Δεδομένων μου`, Catalan `Els Meus Pipelines de
   Dades`) wrap to two lines mid-cycle, then unwrap when a
   shorter string types in next. Surrounding text bounces.
   Fix: shrink the lead font slightly under 640px AND reserve
   enough min-height for two lines so wrapping (if it still
   happens at very narrow widths) does not push siblings down.
   ============================================================ */
@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .prose .lead,
  div.lead,
  [id^="typeit-"] {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.4;
    min-height: 2.9em;
  }
}
